 making.","Jul 15, 2023","Career","src/content/blog/eng-manager.mdx","712539041c505a9e","eng-manager.mdx","minimal-ui",{"id":101,"data":103,"filePath":108,"digest":109,"legacyId":110,"deferredRender":23},{"id":101,"title":104,"description":105,"date":106,"category":107},"The Case for Minimalist User Interfaces","Exploring the psychological benefits of reduced visual noise and how to design content-first experiences that respect user attention.","Sep 12, 2023","Design","src/content/blog/minimal-ui.mdx","6b6bcce12d0029fb","minimal-ui.mdx","perf-nextjs",{"id":111,"data":113,"filePath":118,"digest":119,"legacyId":120,"deferredRender":23},{"id":111,"title":114,"description":115,"date":116,"category":117},"Performance Optimization in Next.js 14","Leveraging the latest features in the App Router to achieve sub-second page loads and perfect Lighthouse scores.","Aug 30, 2023","Infrastructure","src/content/blog/perf-nextjs.mdx","e859c646ccb0f84f","perf-nextjs.mdx","type-safe-events",{"id":121,"data":123,"body":129,"filePath":130,"digest":131,"legacyId":132,"deferredRender":23},{"id":121,"title":124,"description":125,"date":126,"category":127,"readTime":128},"Designing Type-Safe Event Architectures with TypeScript","When building large-scale distributed systems, the communication between services often becomes the bottleneck...","Nov 12, 2024","Engineering","12 min read","When building large-scale distributed systems, the communication between services often becomes the bottleneck for both performance and developer velocity. While REST APIs offer a familiar pattern, they frequently lead to tight coupling and the \"distributed monolith\" anti-pattern.\n\nThe shift toward event-driven architecture (EDA) promises decoupled components, but it often comes at the cost of visibility and type safety. How do we ensure that a producer's payload matches the consumer's expectations without manual schema registries?\n\n## Defining the Schema\n\nWe can leverage TypeScript's advanced type system to create a central truth for our events. By using discriminated unions, we can ensure that every event handler is exhaustive and type-safe.","src/content/blog/type-safe-events.mdx","47539937429c44d8","type-safe-events.mdx"]